The San Diego Zoo has finally unveiled a giant porcupine puppet in Los Angeles, which is believed to be the largest puppet in the world. The puppet, which was unveiled to the public on Tuesday is named Percy the porcupine. It is said to weigh more than a ton and has a circumference of nearly 40 feet. According to the San Diego Zoo officials, the two-story puppet, which is believed to be the world’s largest puppet, is pending for Guinness World Records. Mountain Lion Finally Captured In California OOK Farms Holds Farm To Plate Symposium At IITA The puppet, which features 2,000 foam quills, is scheduled to remain at the park for about a week before moving to its new permanent home at the zoo’s new Wildlife Explorers Base Camp. “This is a wonderful collaboration with the Jim Henson workshop. It’s about a wonderful two-story Brazilian porcupine to inspire the youth about the beauties of wildlife, and connect it, because we couldn’t bring all the animals from the San Diego Zoo here.” San Diego Zoo Wildlife Ambassador, Marco Wendt said.